.TH suspend-emacs 2
.XI suspend-emacs - "Suspend editor and place in background"
.SH NAME
suspend-emacs \- Suspend editor and place in background
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
.B suspend-emacs
.ad
.SH PLATFORM
Supported   on  UNIX   platforms  -   \fIirix\fR,   \fIhpux\fR,   \fIsunos\fR,
\fIfreebsd\fR or \fIlinux\fR.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B suspend-emacs
suspends the editing processor and puts it into the background. The "\fIfg\fR"
command restarts \*(mS. The prompt to suspend is disabled if a \fC0\fR numeric
argument \fIn\fR is given to the command.
